spanishExample: Hay un vaso cerca de la computadora.
englishTranslation: There’s a glass near the computer.

spanishExample: Estoy deseando que me des esos objetos, sobre todo el reloj.
englishTranslation: I’m wishing for you to give me those objects, especially the clock.

spanishExample: Tienes que tener cuidado con el gato.
englishTranslation: You have to be careful with the cat.

spanishExample: Le desea un feliz cumpleaños y le da un reloj.
englishTranslation: She wishes him a happy birthday and gives him a clock.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué estás en la computadora si no comiste tu desayuno?
englishTranslation: Why are you on the computer if you didn’t eat your breakfast?

spanishExample: Prométeme que no lo harás, es absolutamente importante que lo entiendas.
englishTranslation: Promise me you won’t do it, it's absolutely important that you understand it.

spanishExample: Ojalá tuviéramos la llave para esta cerradura.
englishTranslation: I wish we had the key to this lock.

spanishExample: Ellos corren porque no hay platos para el desayuno.
englishTranslation: They are running because there are no plates for breakfast.

spanishExample: No quiero que corran con todos esos objetos.
englishTranslation: I don’t want them to run with all those objects.

spanishExample: Comeremos la cena cuando ella lo desee.
englishTranslation: We’ll eat dinner when she wishes it.

spanishExample: Le desearía lo mejor, pero él no está aquí.
englishTranslation: I’d wish him the best, but he isn’t here.

spanishExample: Quiero que corra porque sus amigos tienen prisa.
englishTranslation: I want him to run because his friends are in a hurry.

spanishExample: Date prisa, ellos no tienen cucharas.
englishTranslation: Hurry up, they don’t have any spoons.

spanishExample: ¿Deseas que nos vayamos?
englishTranslation: Do you wish us to leave?

spanishExample: Había jurado que te di eso ayer.
englishTranslation: I had sworn that I gave you that yesterday.

spanishExample: Quieren que desee muchas cosas, pero yo solo quiero esa llave.
englishTranslation: They want me to wish for many things, but I only want that key.

spanishExample: Él corre porque sabe que esa cerradura no es completamente segura.
englishTranslation: He runs because he knows that lock isn’t completely safe.

spanishExample: Ojalá estemos juntos para el almuerzo; sé que ellos desean lo mismo.
englishTranslation: Hopefully we're together for lunch; I know they wish for the same.

spanishExample: ¡Corran! Son los únicos que tienen la llave.
englishTranslation: (plural) Run! You’re the only ones who have the key.

spanishExample: El gato no ha estado bien últimamente, no ha tocado su plato de comida.
englishTranslation: The cat hasn’t been doing well lately, he hasn’t touched his food dish.

spanishExample: Hay muchísimos tenedores y cuchillos.
englishTranslation: There are a whole lot of forks and knives.

spanishExample: Deseaba llegar temprano, pero la casita está muy lejos.
englishTranslation: I wished to arrive early, but the little house is very far.

spanishExample: Deseaba tener todo lo que le habías prometido.
englishTranslation: She wished to have everything you had promised her.

spanishExample: Me prometiste un tenedor, pero me diste una cuchara.
englishTranslation: You promised me a fork, but you gave me a spoon.

spanishExample: Hay muchísimos vasos, pero necesitamos más cuchillos para el almuerzo.
englishTranslation: There are a whole lot of glasses, but we need more knives for lunch.

spanishExample: Estoy totalmente de acuerdo contigo, te prometo que lo haré durante la cena.
englishTranslation: I totally agree with you, I promise I’ll do it during dinner.
